# UDS Component Completeness Checklist

After the repo restructure, every component lives in **one folder**:
`uds-docs/uds/components/<id>/`. Editing that folder is editing the
component end-to-end. The checklist below ensures the folder stays whole
and consistent.

## Required files in every component folder

- [ ] `<id>.css` â€” token-first component CSS (audited by `audit-token-usage.sh`)
- [ ] `<id>.js` â€” only if the component has interactive behavior
- [ ] `spec.json` â€” conforms to `uds/schemas/spec.schema.json` (the Guidelines tab renders from this)
- [ ] `status.json` â€” `{ current, since, history[] }`
- [ ] `changelog.json` â€” all component history (oldest first), `addedIn` matches `status.history[0].version`
- [ ] `playground.js` â€” exports a default `{ controls, render }` config (used by Playground tab)
- [ ] `examples/manifest.json` â€” conforms to `uds/schemas/manifest.schema.json`
- [ ] `examples/*.html` â€” at least one HTML example file referenced by the manifest

## CSS (`<id>.css`)
- [ ] `:hover` state on interactive elements
- [ ] `:focus-visible` style with `--uds-color-border-outline-focus-visible` on focusable elements
- [ ] `disabled` / `aria-disabled="true"` styling (if applicable)
- [ ] All colors, spacing, fonts, radii use UDS tokens (no hex codes outside `var(--uds-color-X, #fallback)` form)
- [ ] Shadow values use `--uds-shadow-*` tokens

## JS (`<id>.js`) â€” only when interactive
- [ ] IIFE pattern with `window.UDS._init{Name} = init{Name}`
- [ ] `_udsInit` guard (set AFTER validation, not before)
- [ ] Keyboard activation (Enter/Space) for any focusable interactive element
- [ ] Listed in `uds/uds.js` `COMPONENT_SCRIPTS` array (path: `components/<id>/<id>.js`)
- [ ] Wired into `UDS.init()` with the correct selector

## Spec (`spec.json`)
- [ ] Required minimum: `component`, `title`, `description`, `whenToUse`, `whenNotToUse`, `dependencies.css`, `accessibility.keyboard`, `owner`
- [ ] Aim for 80%+ spec completeness before marking Production Ready (see `uds-content-schema.mdc`)
- [ ] `figmaNodeId` set if a deep-link to a specific Figma variant exists
- [ ] `storybookSlug` set once the Storybook story exists
- [ ] `implReference: { exampleId }` points to a real entry in `examples/manifest.json`

## Status (`status.json`)
- [ ] `current` is one of `placeholder | blocked | in-progress | review | production | deprecated`
- [ ] `since` is the UDS version where the current status was entered
- [ ] `history[0].version` matches `addedIn` in `changelog.json`

## Changelog (`changelog.json`)
- [ ] `addedIn` matches the earliest entry's version
- [ ] `entries[]` are oldest-first within the array
- [ ] Each entry has `{ version, type, text }` where type is `added | changed | fixed | deprecated | removed`
- [ ] Re-run `bash scripts/aggregate-changelog.sh` after any changelog edit so `uds/CHANGELOG.json` stays in sync

## Examples (`examples/*.html` + `manifest.json`)
- [ ] At least one `manifest.json` entry has `demoWeight > 0` (so the Demo Builder picks it)
- [ ] Every example file referenced in the manifest exists
- [ ] Every `{{placeholder}}` used in HTML is registered in `uds/schemas/placeholder-vocabulary.json`
- [ ] The set of `udc-*` subpart classes used in examples covers the component's documented API (e.g. nav-header should use bento, search, mywork, account; dropdown should use leading-icon, helper, counter, required when those exist)

## Playground (`playground.js`)
- [ ] Default export is `{ controls: [...], render: function (state) { return { html, code } } }`
- [ ] All controls have `key`, `label`, `type`, `default`
- [ ] Icon-search controls use `type: 'icon-search'`
- [ ] `render(state)` returns vanilla HTML â€” no React/Vue snippets

## Site / app.js wiring (one-time per new component)
- [ ] Sidebar link in `uds-docs/index.html` (under the right group)
- [ ] `<div data-page="<id>" data-page-fragment data-default-tab="examples">...</div>` placeholder in `index.html`
  - The Examples tab content does NOT go in `index.html` â€” it lives in `uds/components/<id>/examples/*.html` and the docs site renders from there

## Pre-commit gate

Run all four audits before committing component changes:

```bash
bash scripts/audit-component-completeness.sh
bash scripts/audit-demo-coverage.sh
bash scripts/audit-placeholders.sh
bash scripts/audit-token-usage.sh
```

All four must exit 0.

## Code quality (vanilla)
- [ ] All `udc-*` class names match the canonical BEM pattern
- [ ] All keyboard interactions in JS match the spec's `accessibility.keyboard` table
- [ ] Realistic data examples for data-consuming components (Data Table, List, Dropdown, Search, Breadcrumb) â€” use the placeholder vocabulary so the Demo Builder can roll varied data
